            PL-SQL INSTALLATION ... (programming language)
            ===================

steps to install PL-SQL
---------------------------
Goto Google.com
Search for "postgresql.org"
    - .org = organization      means providing services without asking for money.
    - .com = commercialization means providing services with asking money.
    - .in  = for india
click on "www.postgrsql.org"
click on hyperlink "Download the installer"
    it will how list of OS and its latest postgrsql's
click on latest postresql of "Windows x86-64"
Downloading of Postgrsql will start and you will find it in "Downloads"

1)  start SQL shell (psql) 
    Server [localhost]:
    Database [postgres]:
    Port [5432]:
    Username [postgres]:
    Password for user postgres:

    psql (17.5)
    WARNING: Console code page (437) differs from Windows code page (1252)
             8-bit characters might not work correctly. See psql reference
             page "Notes for Windows users" for details.
    Type "help" for help.


2)  CREATE cmd
    postgres=# show databases;
    ERROR:  unrecognized configuration parameter "databases"
    postgres=# create database mydb;
    CREATE DATABASE
    postgres=#

3)  complete shell chya baher yene PL-SQL madhe
    postgres=# \q
    Press any key to continue . . .

4)  how to open created database in PL-SQL
    Server [localhost]:
    Database [postgres]: mydb
    Port [5432]:
    Username [postgres]:
    Password for user postgres:

    psql (17.5)
    WARNING: Console code page (437) differs from Windows code page (1252)
             8-bit characters might not work correctly. See psql reference
            page "Notes for Windows users" for details.
    Type "help" for help.

    mydb=#                                  // inside mydb database ...

5)  table === relation ( samanarthi shabt )
    mydb=# \dt                              // db madhe kiti tables ahe check krto \dt 
    Did not find any relations.

6)  check databases available 
    mydb=# \l
                                                            List of databases
      Name    |  Owner   | Encoding | Locale Provider |      Collate       |       Ctype        | Locale | ICU Rules |   Access privileges
    -----------+----------+----------+-----------------+--------------------+--------------------+--------+-----------+-----------------------
    mydb      | postgres | UTF8     | libc            | English_India.1252 | English_India.1252 |        |           |
    postgres  | postgres | UTF8     | libc            | English_India.1252 | English_India.1252 |        |           |
    template0 | postgres | UTF8     | libc            | English_India.1252 | English_India.1252 |        |           | =c/postgres          +
              |          |          |                 |                    |                    |        |           | postgres=CTc/postgres
    template1 | postgres | UTF8     | libc            | English_India.1252 | English_India.1252 |        |           | =c/postgres          +
              |          |          |                 |                    |                    |        |           | postgres=CTc/postgres
    (4 rows)


show tables                                 --> \dt
show databases with default info            --> \l
showing database's names only               --> select datname from pg_database;

7)  existing database chi naav show krto pkt not entire data ...
    pn mulanna hi cmd jaast mahit aste --> "select datname from pg_database;"
    mydb=# select datname from pg_database;     //only for PL-SQL, it includes pg_database i.e., PostgreSQL 
    datname
    -----------
    postgres
    mydb
    template1
    template0
    (4 rows)

8) SQL to find how many database exists
    mydb=# select count (datname) from pg_database;
    count
    -------
        4                                      // no. of database is 4 ...
    (1 row)
    =========================

    ANS :   mydb
            postgres
            template0
            template1

9)
    //Oracle madhe commit fire krave lagtat nhi tr table vgre delete hote sgle.
        - ithe Oracle madhe commit kely shivay data save hot nhi ...
        - first commit and then leave SQL Shell(psql) --> direct X krun screen leave nka kru
            just enter \q and exit ...
        - BUT PL-SQL madhe commit nste. Auto save houn aste tithe.

    mydb=# commit
    mydb-# commit;

    ATM madhe jata tevha lihun yete "transaction failed" pn jevha tumhi pin takta tevha "transaction successful hote" tevha tyala "committed transaction mhntat"